sql:
SELECT energy_type, COUNT(*) AS number_of_sources
FROM energy_sources
GROUP BY energy_type;

external_knowledge:
- "green power plants" refers to renewable energy sources;
- "recent past" in this context refers to the year 2020;
- "typical output levels" imply the average production amounts;
- The query focuses on renewable energy sources only.

sql:
SELECT SUM(production) AS total_production
FROM energy_data
WHERE year_id = (SELECT year_id FROM years WHERE year_name = '2020');
